name: Rosie Case
bio:
A design obsessed Jersey girl in Fort Worth.
All photos are of my home unless otherwise noted.

social_posts.post_text: Howdy friends…popping out of insta-retirement because Georgie the elder statesman was in the right place at the right time, and I love him so. Guernica-inspired horse mask/sculpture snagged by my sis @part_time_italian in Venezia. I hope you’re all well!
Sometimes you go to Facebook marketplace looking for nightstands, and it gives you “The Leaning Man” lifesize cubist sculpture instead. What’re ya gonna do? 🙃

This final manic post coming to you from funghi forest, conveniently located opposite my bed. If you’re a fan of mushroom decor like yours truly, launch yourself out into the retail wilds—they’re sprouting up just about everywhere right now.

I’ve been working on trying to get my guest room in shape, using things I already have. I creep in here at night with a glass of wine and stare without blinking, then furiously start peppering the drywall with nail holes only to stare more and change my mind. It has also become the landing place for my little collection of Venetian masks, which have long gone without a home. A big bad wolf can be partially seen there to the right.
New acquisitions. 👀 My husband said that these eyes resemble SpongeBob’s, and I am comfortable with this association.
Coastal: Food chain edition. In this world, lemons are at the bottom. Pop of color via the melamine dishes and tray from @thomas.fuchs.homegoods Chairs snagged from @thebeauideal
When @thriftwiththemakerista posted this massive bronze stegosaurus on her stories from an antiquing trip to the UK a few weeks ago, I lost my prehistoric marbles…and now it roams about stateside.
Pining for temps below 100° and swapping out coffee tables. This one a favorite from @thebeauideal. 💙

Alright, I know that I’m such a weirdo not posting for weeks or months on end, and then multiple times in one day, but this shady character arrived fresh from eBay and I had to put him into action. For context, it’s standing on a coffee table, and is about 16 inches high. He reminds me of the sinister guy on the old neighborhood watch signs. 👀

A design obsessed Jersey girl in Fort Worth.
All photos are of my home unless otherwise noted.
